// Local, per-developer macOS code-signing override (NOT committed).
//
// Included by AppInfo.xcconfig via `#include? "Signing.local.xcconfig"`. Signs
// local dev builds with a trusted, team-prefixed identity so the macOS
// data-protection keychain (lib/core/providers/storage_providers.dart) reads the
// app's secrets with NO prompt. An ad-hoc / no-team build can't satisfy the
// keychain-access-groups entitlement (errSecMissingEntitlement, -34018).
//
// Don't edit this .example. Run, once:
//     bash macos/scripts/create_local_signing_cert.sh [TEAM_ID]
// It writes the real (git-ignored) Signing.local.xcconfig:
//
//     CODE_SIGN_STYLE = Automatic
//     DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = <your-team-id>
//     CODE_SIGN_IDENTITY = Apple Development
//
// Local dev always uses AUTOMATIC signing (free or paid account). Manual /
// Developer ID can't be used locally: the keychain-access-groups "Keychain
// Sharing" capability forces a provisioning profile under manual signing, which
// `flutter run` can't mint. Automatic signing auto-provisions it; you mint the
// profile once with xcodebuild -allowProvisioningUpdates (the script prints how).
//
// The debug entitlement uses $(DEVELOPMENT_TEAM), so your team auto-fills the
// keychain access group — no source edits. CI ignores this file (builds ad-hoc,
// then re-signs Developer ID in scripts/release/macos_package.sh).
